              "text": "The nzumari, like the chivoti, is decorated. The bells attached to the instrument feature carved geometric designs, and the overall appearance of a well-made nzumari reflects the Digo understanding that musical instruments are not merely functional objects but works of art that honour the ceremonies they serve."
