              "text": "Of all the crafts practiced by the Digo, pottery may be the oldest. Long before mangrove poles were cut for house frames and coral was quarried for walls, human hands were shaping clay into vessels for cooking, storage, and ceremony. The Digo pottery tradition belongs to this deep human inheritance, but it carries its own distinctive character — shaped by the specific clays of the Shimba Hills, the specific foods of the coast, and the specific social structures that determine who holds this knowledge and how it is transmitted."
