              "type": "paragraph",
              "text": "The basic unit of Digo settlement is the mudzi — the homestead. A mudzi is not a single house but a cluster of structures belonging to an extended family, organized around a central clearing. The elder's round hut occupies a position of prominence. Rectangular houses for married sons and their families are arranged nearby. Cooking areas, grain stores, and animal shelters complete the compound. The whole is typically enclosed by a living fence of planted shrubs or a woven barrier, marking the boundary between domestic space and the wider world."
