              "text": "The Digo are the only predominantly Muslim group among the nine Mijikenda peoples. They are also the group with the strongest matrilineal traditions. These two facts create a tension that has shaped Digo society for centuries and continues to define the most intimate decisions of family life: who inherits, who holds authority over children, whose law governs when a marriage ends or a patriarch dies."
