              "text": "The tensions between matrilineal custom and Islamic law were significant enough to require formal intervention at the highest level of Kenya's Islamic judiciary. The Chief Kadhi stepped in to establish inheritance frameworks for children of mixed-faith marriages — cases where one parent followed matrilineal custom and the other followed Islamic law, where the question of which system applied was genuinely unclear."
